        <h1>King - Man + Woman = Queen</h1>
        <h2><a href="/game_questions/<%= Time.now.to_i %><%= rand(10000) %>">Play game</a></h2>
        <h2>Objective:</h2>
        <p>Match words based on specific relationships, such as opposites, synonyms, categories, and more, to find the correct final word.</p>

        <h2>How to Play:</h2>

        <h3>1. Understanding the Format:</h3>
        <p>Each puzzle is presented in the format: <strong>Word1 - Word2 + Word3 = ?</strong><br>
        Your goal is to determine the correct word that fits in place of the <strong>?</strong>.</p>

        <h3>2. Word Relationships:</h3>
        <ul style="list-style-type: none;">
            <li><strong>Opposites:</strong> Identify the opposite of the first word when adjusted by the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Hot - Summer + Winter = Cold</em></li>
            <li><strong>Synonyms:</strong> Find a synonym of the first word when adjusted by the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Big - Large + Tiny = Small</em></li>
            <li><strong>Categories:</strong> Determine the word that fits into the category defined by the adjustment of the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Dog - Pet + Feline = Cat</em></li>
            <li><strong>Superlatives:</strong> Adjust the first word to its opposite meaning based on the adjustments from the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Good - Better + Worst = Bad</em></li>
            <li><strong>Relationships:</strong> Define a relationship similar to the first word, adjusted by the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Father - Parent + Child = Son</em></li>
            <li><strong>Occupations:</strong> Relate the occupation to the result of adjusting with the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Doctor - Physician + Illness = Patient</em></li>
            <li><strong>Materials:</strong> Determine the material that results from the transformation.
                <br>Example: <em>Wood - Oak + Steel = Metal</em></li>
            <li><strong>Shapes:</strong> Find the shape that matches the relationship after adjustments.
                <br>Example: <em>Circle - Round + Square = Rectangle</em></li>
            <li><strong>Numbers:</strong> Calculate the correct number by adjusting the first with the second and third.
                <br>Example: <em>Two - Pair + Single = One</em></li>
            <li><strong>Colors:</strong> Identify the color that corresponds to the adjustments.
                <br>Example: <em>Red - Warm + Cool = Blue</em></li>
            <li><strong>Times of Day:</strong> Determine the time of day based on the relationships.
                <br>Example: <em>Morning - Dawn + Dusk = Evening</em></li>
            <li><strong>Seasons:</strong> Adjust the season to find the correct final one.
                <br>Example: <em>Winter - Cold + Hot = Summer</em></li>
            <li><strong>Fruits and Vegetables:</strong> Find the correct food item based on the relationship.
                <br>Example: <em>Apple - Fruit + Leafy = Lettuce</em></li>
            <li><strong>Locations:</strong> Identify the location by adjusting the first with the second and third words.
                <br>Example: <em>Mountain - High + Low = Valley</em></li>
            <li><strong>Emotions:</strong> Determine the emotion that fits after the adjustment.
                <br>Example: <em>Joy - Happiness + Anger = Rage</em></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Answer Submission:</h3>
        <p>Players must submit their answer for the final word that correctly completes the equation.<br>
        Answers should be exact, considering spelling and the relationship indicated by the puzzle.</p>

        <h3>4. Scoring:</h3>
        <p>Points are awarded for each correct answer.<br>
        Bonus points may be awarded for consecutive correct answers, especially for more complex relationships.</p>
